Comment: My opponent was a little kid and  sometimes I will play this instead of Nf3 to see if it throws them. If I see  2...Nc6, ...d6, or ...e6 then I will play 3. d4/4.Nd4 right away, but  sometimes odd things happen and then you can play d3/g3/Bg2 and play a closed  Sicilian if your opponent seems uncomfortable.
